doc.after: Harold would have been celebrating his victory at Stamford Bridge on the night of 26/27 September 1066, while William of Normandy's invasion fleet set sail for England on the morning of 27 September 1066.[150] Harold marched his army back down to the south coast where he met William's army, at a place now called Battle just outside Hastings.[145] Harold was killed when he fought and lost the Battle of Hastings on 14 October 1066.[151]
